00:25:34,730 --> 00:25:36,860
Like he left
the credit cards behind.

467
00:25:37,270 --> 00:25:39,790
I mean,
why does a street robber
grab money from a wallet

468
00:25:39,870 --> 00:25:41,860
and leave the credit cards?

469
00:25:42,210 --> 00:25:45,470
They're won'th a pretty
good piece of change
on the black market.

470
00:25:45,540 --> 00:25:46,700
You see what I mean, sir?

471
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:49,110
Credit cards. What else?

472
00:25:49,310 --> 00:25:51,940
Oh, there was
an alligator bag.

473
00:25:52,020 --> 00:25:53,680
A diamond ring.

474
00:25:54,390 --> 00:25:57,720
I doubt very much
if a robber in a hurry,
on the edge of panic,

475
00:25:57,790 --> 00:26:01,750
is gonna take the time
to pull the ring off
of Claire's finger.

476
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:03,520
You mean, sir...

477
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:07,320
You mean, if she was dead,
he couldn't get it off?

478
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:08,920
Well, she is,
I believe, isn't she?

479
00:26:09,070 --> 00:26:11,330
Well, yes, sir.
But he could have
asked her for it first.

480
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:13,100
Before he shot her.

481
00:26:13,170 --> 00:26:17,570
I remember Claire trying
to get that ring off
at a party once.

482
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:19,800
Some silly game people
were playing.

483
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:21,780
She couldn't.
Not even with soap.

484
00:26:22,310 --> 00:26:24,140
And you can check that out
with her husband.

485
00:26:24,650 --> 00:26:26,580
He was the one that asked her
to take it off.

486
00:26:26,820 --> 00:26:28,980
He was on the other team.

487
00:26:29,150 --> 00:26:30,880
Boy, when you say you studied,

488
00:26:30,960 --> 00:26:32,580
you aren't kidding,
are you, sir?

489
00:26:33,220 --> 00:26:35,350
Well, then, what about
the alligator bag?

490
00:26:35,430 --> 00:26:37,360
An alligator bag
that is six years old

491
00:26:37,430 --> 00:26:38,760
is apt to be worn-looking.

492
00:26:38,830 --> 00:26:40,060
It doesn't look
like it's won'th very much.

493
00:26:40,130 --> 00:26:41,430
It probably isn't.

494
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:44,530
How do you happen
to know all that much
about her bag, sir?

495
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,330
I gave it to her.

496
00:26:47,570 --> 00:26:50,440
Well, that takes care of that,
doesn't it?

497
00:26:50,510 --> 00:26:54,670
Right. Well,
I guess, then

498
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:56,470
there's only
the credit cards, sir.

499
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,870
If the killer is an idiot.

500
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:00,770
I beg your pardon, sir,

501
00:27:00,850 --> 00:27:02,440
I don't quite follow
your meaning there.

502
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:06,190
Well, you don't
kill a woman

503
00:27:06,260 --> 00:27:09,920
and then sell the credit cards
with her name on it.

504
00:27:11,230 --> 00:27:14,220
The police have been known
to bribe fences before,
you know.

505
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:17,390
Well, of course.
I'm sorry, sir.

506
00:27:17,470 --> 00:27:18,990
I should've thought
of that myself.

507
00:27:19,470 --> 00:27:21,200
Jeez, I guess you're right,
aren't you?

508
00:27:21,270 --> 00:27:22,970
Not a lot to go on,
is there?

509
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:25,030
Cup of coffee?

510
00:27:26,710 --> 00:27:28,040
Sir?

511
00:27:30,010 --> 00:27:31,540
Except the panic.

512
00:27:31,620 --> 00:27:32,640
The panic?

513
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,740
Yes, sir.
I might have something
in this area.

514
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:36,250
See what you think.

515
00:27:37,150 --> 00:27:39,520
Mrs. Daley was shot
at a distance of 30 feet

516
00:27:39,590 --> 00:27:41,220
and she was shot
in the back.

517
00:27:41,290 --> 00:27:42,590
Are you with me
so far?

518
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:44,250
Yes, I think
I can grasp that.

519
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:45,560
Now,

520
00:27:46,430 --> 00:27:48,630
Tony...

521
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:50,530
He's the owner
of the deli.

522
00:27:51,100 --> 00:27:53,900
He said that the killer
was "cool as a cucumber."

523
00:27:54,100 --> 00:27:57,070
That's a direct quote, sir.

524
00:27:57,370 --> 00:28:01,210
So that means that
when Mrs. Daley
tried to run,

525
00:28:01,550 --> 00:28:03,380
that's when
he lost his cool.

526
00:28:04,450 --> 00:28:06,780
See, that's when he panicked
and he shot her.

527
00:28:07,380 --> 00:28:09,720
But he hit her
right in the heart, sir,

528
00:28:09,790 --> 00:28:12,780
and at the distance of 30 feet
while she was running.

529
00:28:13,590 --> 00:28:15,620
Now, that's hard
to do in a panic.

530
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:17,730
What do you think?

531
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:19,630
I think that I had better
try and help you

532
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:22,130
because you're going
to ask me to, aren't you?

533
00:28:22,370 --> 00:28:24,330
You did it again, sir.
You read my mind.

534
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:27,030
Would you?
Oh, that would be an honor.

535
00:28:27,100 --> 00:28:29,660
Detective Lucerne
helping me.

536
00:28:29,740 --> 00:28:31,370
Wait till I tell my wife.

537
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:32,700
Somebody
asking for me?

538
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:35,870
Oh, Sid,
it's all right.

539
00:28:36,350 --> 00:28:39,440
This is
Lieutenant Columbo
from the police department.

540
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:41,880
This is Claire's husband,
Sid Daley.

541
00:28:41,950 --> 00:28:44,790
Sid, what can I tell you?
You know how I...

542
00:28:44,990 --> 00:28:46,150
How I felt
about Claire, huh?

543
00:28:46,220 --> 00:28:47,710
ASSISTANT DIRECTOR:
We're ready, Mr. Fowler!

544
00:28:47,790 --> 00:28:49,690
Yeah. Yeah,
I'll be right there.

545
00:28:49,830 --> 00:28:50,890
Whoops!

546
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:52,620
We're hooked.

547
00:28:52,700 --> 00:28:55,530
I'm terribly sorry
to have this happen
at such a tense moment.

548
00:28:55,930 --> 00:28:57,330
Mr. Fowler, we're ready!

549
00:28:57,400 --> 00:28:59,230
I said,
I'll be there.

550
00:28:59,300 --> 00:29:01,200
I'd better watch this,
Lieutenant. Do you mind?

551
00:29:02,970 --> 00:29:04,300
SID: What's the story, huh?

552
00:29:04,380 --> 00:29:06,070
ASSISTANT DIRECTOR:
We're running
a little late, Sidney.

553
00:29:06,140 --> 00:29:07,410
Let's move it, huh?

554
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:12,410
Lieutenant,
what about this robber?

555
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,710
Do you have
any leads?

556
00:29:14,490 --> 00:29:16,040
Well, sir...

557
00:29:16,150 --> 00:29:18,880
The truth is, it seems to be
a little bit more complicated

558
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:20,010
than a robbery, sir.

559
00:29:20,090 --> 00:29:22,020
Oh?
What the Lieutenant is saying

560
00:29:22,090 --> 00:29:23,790
is that he's come
to the conclusion

561
00:29:23,860 --> 00:29:27,130
that Claire may have been
murdered and the robbery
may be a cover-up.

562
00:29:27,530 --> 00:29:29,360
Murdered?

563
00:29:30,030 --> 00:29:31,500
That's insane.

564
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,870
Don't you think
you should have come to me
first with this, Lieutenant?

565
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:39,170
Well, I tried to, sir.
I've been looking for you
ever since last night.

566
00:29:40,210 --> 00:29:42,740
I was with my lawyer
last night.

567
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:45,510
We meet for chess
once or twice a month,

568
00:29:45,780 --> 00:29:48,150
and last night turned out
to be a marathon session.

569
00:29:48,290 --> 00:29:50,150
We didn't quit
until five in the morning,

570
00:29:50,220 --> 00:29:51,210
so I stayed over.

571
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:53,050
Thank you, sir.

572
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:54,650
This friend,
sir, the lawyer,

573
00:29:54,730 --> 00:29:56,060
where can I
reach him?

574
00:29:57,330 --> 00:29:59,090
SID: Is this
a grilling session?

575
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:00,930
What am I?
Some kind of suspect
or something?

576
00:30:02,100 --> 00:30:03,830
Nothing personal, sir.

577
00:30:03,900 --> 00:30:06,390
I have to ask
these routine questions.

578
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:09,300
Well, his name is Leo Hart.

579
00:30:09,370 --> 00:30:11,970
But I think you're gonna
have trouble contacting him.

580
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:14,680
He took the plane
for Rome at noon.

581
00:30:15,410 --> 00:30:16,500
ASSISTANT DIRECTOR:
We're ready to roll.

582
00:30:16,580 --> 00:30:17,570
Let's do it then, huh?

583
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:21,280
Mark! Why don't you
entertain the Lieutenant
while we shoot this.

584
00:30:21,350 --> 00:30:22,880
I'm sure he's
seen this, anyway.

585
00:30:22,950 --> 00:30:24,220
Seen it?
He was in it.

586
00:30:26,860 --> 00:30:29,520
Yeah, you know,
Ward is right.

587
00:30:29,660 --> 00:30:32,030
Time is my business, you know,
and I always know it.

588
00:30:32,330 --> 00:30:33,990
Oh, boy,
am I hung-over today.

589
00:30:34,060 --> 00:30:36,030
I'll be glad
when this day's over.

590
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:38,660
Hey, what time you got,
Lieutenant?

591
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:41,230
11:00 on the dot.

592
00:30:41,310 --> 00:30:42,700
Are you kidding?

593
00:30:42,770 --> 00:30:45,330
Jeez, I paid a thousand
smackers for this watch.

594
00:30:45,610 --> 00:30:47,270
I lost five minutes
overnight.

595
00:30:48,050 --> 00:30:49,340
Do you mind,
sir?

596
00:30:49,450 --> 00:30:51,640
I have never seen
a thousand dollar
watch before.

597
00:30:53,980 --> 00:30:56,080
Boy, that must
be solid gold.

598
00:30:56,220 --> 00:30:57,450
That's platinum.

599
00:30:57,520 --> 00:30:59,420
Oh, no wonder
it looks so different.

600
00:31:01,690 --> 00:31:03,630
Well, there's nothing wrong
with your watch, sir.

601
00:31:03,730 --> 00:31:05,130
You have
11:00, too.

602
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:07,290
Yeah, but it should be
five minutes past eleven.

603
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:10,230
I always set my watch,
you know, five minutes fast.

604
00:31:10,330 --> 00:31:13,570
You know, you're always
racing against time
24 hours a day.

605
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:16,900
Excuse me, sir,
are those men
members of your crew?

606
00:31:16,970 --> 00:31:19,140
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
They're with us all the time.

607
00:31:19,540 --> 00:31:21,940
Good. I think I'll have
a word with them.

608
00:31:22,010 --> 00:31:23,310
Thank you very much
for everything.

609
00:31:27,580 --> 00:31:31,110
Excuse me, sir.
Lieutenant Columbo, LAPD.

610
00:31:31,220 --> 00:31:32,590
I wonder if I can have
a word with you?

611
00:31:32,790 --> 00:31:35,160
MAN 1: We're gonna
have the hotel
in the shot, right?

612
00:31:35,230 --> 00:31:36,250
MAN 2: Everything.

613
00:31:36,330 --> 00:31:37,420
On the master, right?

614
00:31:37,490 --> 00:31:38,650
In the master, right.
Okay.

615
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:41,760
This is where...
He comes up right here.

616
00:31:41,830 --> 00:31:43,090
Can I ask you this?

617
00:31:43,230 --> 00:31:44,430
What now?

618
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:45,930
This is just the way
we discussed it.

619
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:49,130
This we do on stage...
This is on stage three, right?

620
00:31:49,210 --> 00:31:50,610
Right. Stage three.

621
00:31:50,670 --> 00:31:54,580
How long do we stay there?
Two days at the most.
Then we go to four.

622
00:31:54,650 --> 00:31:57,980
Well, what I wanna know...
Would you make a note
of this, Cathy?

623
00:31:58,050 --> 00:31:59,810
What I wanna know
is do we really
need this set?

624
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:01,440
Excuse me, sir.
I don't wanna
interrupt you.

625
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:03,150
Is that the
shark from <i>Jaws?</i>

626
00:32:03,220 --> 00:32:04,350
Yeah, I believe it is,
Lieutenant.

627
00:32:04,420 --> 00:32:05,950
That's the one
that they used
in the picture?

628
00:32:06,020 --> 00:32:07,150
I think so.

629
00:32:07,220 --> 00:32:08,990
Well, that looks
different to me.

630
00:32:09,060 --> 00:32:10,080
I can't help that.

631
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:11,220
If we do scene 31
on stage four...

632
00:32:11,300 --> 00:32:12,390
Could they have two?

633
00:32:12,460 --> 00:32:14,060
I...
You know,
because in the picture...

634
00:32:14,130 --> 00:32:15,690
Lieutenant...
...at the end,
it got all mangled.

635
00:32:15,770 --> 00:32:17,860
Lieutenant, I know
you didn't come here
to talk about sharks.

636
00:32:17,940 --> 00:32:19,730
I'm pressed for time.
What do you want?

637
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:21,960
Well, I just wanted
to ask a couple questions...

638
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:23,470
We got wardrobe
in five minutes.

639
00:32:23,540 --> 00:32:24,800
I can give you
two minutes.

640
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:25,860
Fine.

641
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:28,240
Thank you
very much.

642
00:32:28,310 --> 00:32:30,280
I understand, sir,

643
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:32,340
that you and your wife
were living apart.

644
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:34,740
That's true, Lieutenant.

645
00:32:34,850 --> 00:32:36,650
We haven't been close
for some time now.

646
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:38,450
Would you
know, sir,

647
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:40,110
whether or not
she was seeing somebody?

648
00:32:40,190 --> 00:32:41,450
I don't mean
to get personal,

649
00:32:41,530 --> 00:32:44,490
but somebody whom
she might be emotionally
involved with?

650
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:46,690
Claire was devoted
to her work, Lieutenant.

651
00:32:46,900 --> 00:32:48,990
She wasrt any more
interested in lovers

652
00:32:49,070 --> 00:32:50,660
than she was
in her husband.

653
00:32:50,730 --> 00:32:53,530
It made for a pretty
miserable marriage.

654
00:32:54,370 --> 00:32:56,340
Well, still, you must've
gotten along pretty good.

655
00:32:56,410 --> 00:32:58,000
I mean, you were
partners in business.

656
00:32:58,080 --> 00:33:00,700
Partners?
That was on paper, Lieutenant.

657
00:33:01,150 --> 00:33:02,910
Claire fought me
on everything.

658
00:33:03,510 --> 00:33:04,880
She had to have things
done her way.

659
00:33:04,950 --> 00:33:06,680
If I said white,
she'd say black.

660
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:09,650
All you have to do
is take a look at this new
Ward Fowler contract.

661
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:13,380
Paying an actor
that kind of money
is insanity.

662
00:33:13,660 --> 00:33:16,650
Now, wait a minute.
Let me get this straight.

663
00:33:17,590 --> 00:33:20,590
Are you saying that you didn't
wanna pay him that money?

664
00:33:20,660 --> 00:33:22,290
I think they should
have turned him down.

665
00:33:22,370 --> 00:33:24,030
I think he would have folded.

666
00:33:24,100 --> 00:33:26,470
But Claire argued me
right under the table.

667
00:33:26,570 --> 00:33:28,370
I was an idiot
for giving in.

668
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:30,200
Now, if this show
takes a dip
they'll drop it.

669
00:33:30,270 --> 00:33:32,040
I still don't understand.

670
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:35,400
You and your wife
were partners.

671
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:37,310
Now, isn't it
to her best interest

672
00:33:37,380 --> 00:33:39,180
not to give him
all that money?

673
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:43,380
In anything involving Ward,
she always took his side.

674
00:33:47,060 --> 00:33:49,150
Forgive me
for asking this, sir.

675
00:33:50,530 --> 00:33:52,190
I seem to remember stories

676
00:33:52,260 --> 00:33:53,990
that at one time
they were pretty close.

677
00:33:54,060 --> 00:33:56,760
Are you suggesting
that their relationship

678
00:33:56,830 --> 00:33:58,560
was still pretty close?

679
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:00,260
Yeah.
But not the way you mean it,
Lieutenant.

680
00:34:00,340 --> 00:34:02,530
Oh, sure, they'd
had a big romance,

681
00:34:02,610 --> 00:34:05,440
but by the time
I came into the picture,
it was dead.

682
00:34:05,510 --> 00:34:07,600
But that didn't mean
that Claire was finished

683
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:09,410
watching over Ward's career.

684
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:12,280
She stopped being a lover
and she became a mother.

685
00:34:12,350 --> 00:34:14,210
Sent him off to have
his teeth capped.

686
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:16,080
Made him drop ten pounds.

687
00:34:16,190 --> 00:34:17,550
Showed him how
to comb his hair.

688
00:34:17,620 --> 00:34:19,820
It sounds like
she was proud of him.

689
00:34:20,060 --> 00:34:21,180
It was ego.

690
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:23,150
Claire's ego.

691
00:34:24,460 --> 00:34:25,450
You learn.

692
00:34:27,830 --> 00:34:28,890
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

693
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:34,960
Lieutenant Columbo.

694
00:34:35,510 --> 00:34:37,700
MAN: No problem.
No problem.

695
00:34:37,770 --> 00:34:40,540
COLUMBO:
Lieutenant Lucerne.

696
00:34:44,310 --> 00:34:45,780
I just wanted
to fill you in, sir.

697
00:34:46,720 --> 00:34:48,210
Right.
What have we got?

698
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:49,850
Nothing.

699
00:34:50,690 --> 00:34:52,550
We still think
it was premeditated,
don't we?

700
00:34:52,720 --> 00:34:56,060
Oh, I don't know, sir.
What do you suppose?

701
00:34:57,160 --> 00:35:00,250
Well, I suppose
if that's your instinct,
then it must be right.

702
00:35:00,330 --> 00:35:02,460
My instinct
about Claire,

703
00:35:02,530 --> 00:35:04,800
and I don't have
any clues to go on,

704
00:35:04,870 --> 00:35:08,200
is that she was
what they call,

705
00:35:08,270 --> 00:35:10,500
I believe the term
is victim-prone.

706
00:35:11,170 --> 00:35:12,440
Some people are,
you know?

707
00:35:12,510 --> 00:35:16,000
And Claire, well,

708
00:35:17,450 --> 00:35:19,140
Claire was given
to taunting people.

709
00:35:20,250 --> 00:35:21,740
She was a born victim.

710
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:25,420
She was the kind
who asks for it.

711
00:35:25,490 --> 00:35:26,680
In her marriage,
in her life...

712
00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:28,020
Quite possibly
in her death.

